cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.CE, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of weighted proportional fairness to data flows in the Internet and proposes ways of weighting TCP connections. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of differentiated services in the Internet. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to differentiated services. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper discusses the maximisation of utility in the network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the theoretical aspects of proportional fairness and its application in the Internet.
